summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions 1177 (1998), 1226 (1999) and 1227 (1999),

Deeply disturbed by renewed Eritrea-Ethiopia fighting,

Stressing need for peaceful conflict resolution,

Reaffirming commitment to Eritrea and Ethiopia's sovereignty, independence and territorial integrity,

Supporting Organization of African Unity (OAU) efforts,

Welcoming its Mission's report,

Concerned about humanitarian implications,

Stressing situation threatens peace and security,

 Condemns renewed fighting (para 1); 

Demands immediate ceasefire and refraining from force (para 2); 

Demands substantive peace talks under OAU auspices (para 3); 

Threatens further steps within 72 hours if hostilities continue (para 4); 

Supports OAU, Algeria, and other parties (para 5); 

Endorses Framework Agreement and Modalities (para 6); 

Endorses OAU's 5 May 2000 Communiqu√© (para 7); 

Calls for civilian safety, human rights and humanitarian law respect (para 8); 

Requests Secretary-General's regular updates (para 9); 

Decides to remain seized (para 10).
